Long-term pointer ledger

Purpose:
- Local durable-memory map for docs, reports, release evidence, and hosted MATM routing.

Last verified: 2026-07-09
Memory scope: local durable documentation pointers and promotion rules.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this local ledger when durable docs/reports change; submit public-safe durable summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: `docs/long-term-memory`, `docs/reports`, `.uai/long-term-memory.uai`, and `.uai/totem.uai`.
Next action for agents: promote facts only after code, docs, tests, release notes, or reviewed reports prove them.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, or raw one-time keys.

Durable docs memory root:
- docs/long-term-memory/

Initial records:
- docs/long-term-memory/project-charter.md
- docs/long-term-memory/architecture-notes.md
- docs/long-term-memory/release-verification-summary.md
- .uai/long-term-memory.uai
- sites/multiagentmemory.com/README.md

Release evidence:
- docs/reports/final-verification-report.md
- docs/reports/local-route-verification.json
- docs/reports/live-route-verification.json

Hosted memory:
- MemoryEndpoints.com is the mid-to-long-term MATM memory endpoint for this project.
- MultiAgentMemory.com is documentation only and should point agents back to MemoryEndpoints.com for hosted memory operations.
- Repository layout documentation lives at docs/repository-structure.md.
- Totem invariant: local `.uai` stays active always and is never retired by hosted MATM verification.

Promotion rule:
Facts in session memory become durable only after they are written to docs, code, tests, release notes, or reviewed reports.
